<br>
Try this link to learn more about research,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/">mythiran.allakhazam.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
As mentioned above, check some other info on other sites too.  <br>
<br>
If you are using Casters Realm for spell info,  DO NOT trust them, they are very often wrong, especially about where to find/buy spells.  Even the people posting info about spells on that sight seem to know jack sh*t.<br>
<br>
I personally believe the best way to get your research up is to NOT train in it until 24, and DO NOT spend practice points from the begining of your life except for the basic skills you have to train to learn ie Meditate, dodge etc. By waiting until 23 you get the full 24 for 1st point and just keep using your points each level.  Even with your skill maxed for your current level you will have failures on spell combines for that same level though.  It is best to collect the components, and ask another higher level mage if he would help by doing the combine.  I rarely had to wait for long before finding someone, just have all the items in your combine book ready to go and they will usually be happy to do it.<br>
<br>
While it is true you can RESEARCH the spell yourself, it is BEST to just BUY it.  You will spend more time playing and having fun than running around trying to find components.   <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=429815">Talena Waterflower</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - 55 Myrmidon<br>
